# ZenAI Core — Compiled Distribution
#
# Build:
#     python dist_build/build_wheel.py
#
# This produces:
#     dist_build/dist/zenai_core-1.0.0-cp3XX-win_amd64.whl
#
# Collaborators install with:
#     pip install zenai_core-1.0.0-cp311-cp311-win_amd64.whl[full]
#
# What's inside the wheel:
#     rag_core/       → Compiled RAG engine (.pyd, not .py)
#     local_llm/      → Compiled LLM management (.pyd)
#     Core/           → Compiled models + services (.pyd)
#     zenai_adapters/ → Compiled adapter layer (.pyd)
#
# No source code is distributed. Only __init__.py stubs
# (for package discovery) and native .pyd/.so binaries.
#
# Prerequisites for building (not for installing):
#     pip install cython setuptools wheel
#     Visual Studio Build Tools (C++ desktop workload)
#
# Optional runtime deps (install as extras):
#     pip install zenai_core[full]     # everything
#     pip install zenai_core[rag]      # RAG only
#     pip install zenai_core[llm]      # LLM only
